&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Junior Analyst&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alpha Alternatives&lt;/strong&gt; is the specialist alternatives advisory business of Alpha FMC, the leading global consultancy to the asset management, wealth management and insurance industries. Focused on alternative investments and financial services, we help clients deliver operational excellence through expertise in structure, process and technology.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Working with leading firms across the alternatives market, we provide project-based services spanning business consulting, technology solutions and end-to-end operational improvement. Our teams combine deep industry knowledge with hands-on delivery experience to help clients solve complex challenges and drive meaningful change.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As part of Alpha FMC, we offer the opportunity to work in a high-performing, collaborative and entrepreneurial environment where individuals are given real responsibility, strong support and the chance to build deep expertise in a growing and evolving market.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic &lt;strong&gt;AI Junior Analyst&lt;/strong&gt; to join our growing team. This is a pivotal role supporting multiple service lines across the firm, working closely with consulting teams, service line owners, client segment stakeholders and central programme leads to identify, prioritise and deliver AI use cases that create value across the business.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The successful candidate will help drive practical AI adoption across a range of business areas, including advisory engagements and enterprise performance management, while contributing to broader governance, collaboration and continuous improvement efforts.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with service line owners, client segment stakeholders and consulting teams to identify and deliver prioritised AI initiatives that address operational and strategic challenges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage a centralised prompt repository and technical playbook, demonstrating how source data can be transformed into client-ready deliverables using AI tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use coding skills, including &lt;strong&gt;Python&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;SQL&lt;/strong&gt;, alongside workflow automation technologies to design scalable AI solutions for consulting teams and enterprise functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage multiple concurrent AI projects with a strong focus on quality, consistency and timely delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a bridge between onshore consulting teams, offshore technical resources and central programme groups, sharing best practice and identifying opportunities for broader AI adoption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal discussions on AI capabilities, helping stakeholders understand use cases, value potential and practical application across the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the continuous improvement of AI ways of working, ensuring lessons learned and reusable assets are shared across teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;We are looking for a recent graduate or early-career professional with:&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A degree in &lt;strong&gt;Computer Science, Data Science, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning&lt;/strong&gt;, or a related technical field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on familiarity with &lt;strong&gt;AI and natural language processing tools&lt;/strong&gt;, particularly &lt;strong&gt;GPT-based applications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in &lt;strong&gt;Python&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;SQL&lt;/strong&

&lt;p&gt;Alpha FMC is the leading global consultancy to the Asset Management, Wealth Management and Insurance industries. As a trusted partner to more than 95% of the top 20 global Asset Management firms by AUM, we have an unrivalled track record in providing our base of over 660 clients with a competitive edge by using our deep industry knowledge and expertise. We have the largest dedicated team in the industry, with nearly 650 consultants globally, operating from 15 offices spanning the UK, Europe, North America and Asia. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Alpha, diversity and inclusion is not only important for – but critical to – our success, and we are committed to employing individuals from all backgrounds to reflect the multi-cultural society we live in. We have worked hard to foster an environment that welcomes everyone and celebrates each other’s successes.&amp;nbsp; We want Alpha to not only feel like ‘a job’ – we want it to feel like a community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;What makes us different?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Established yet entrepreneurial. &lt;/strong&gt;We believe that Alpha is the perfect combination of a successfully established firm (founded in 2003, quoted on the AIM of the London Stock Exchange) whilst being entrepreneurial, dynamic, and growing – meaning your contribution is seen and valued.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work alongside the best in the industry.&lt;/strong&gt; Working at Alpha gives you the opportunity to work alongside not only the leading organisations in our industry, but also experts within the Alpha team. Learning directly from both will allow you to develop your own expertise in our space.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A true meritocracy. &lt;/strong&gt;At Alpha, we don’t have any concept of ‘time at level’ or promotion quotas – which means that your potential is truly driven by your performance rather than anything else!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High responsibility and autonomy. &lt;/strong&gt;Given our project team sizes (typically 2-10 people), each member has a high level of responsibility and autonomy on every project, as well as exposure to senior team members (e.g. Directors) who continuously train and develop you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Culture and community. &lt;/strong&gt;We pride ourselves on creating a supportive, nurturing environment where people can be themselves.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alpha Alternatives &amp;amp; Role Overview&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alpha Alternatives is a global advisory firm with a focus on alternative investments and financial services. Our business model combines the talents of industry leaders and experts in service delivery to assist clients in achieving operational efficiencies and excellence through structure, process, and technology. We provide project-based services in several key areas including business consulting, technology solutions, and end-to-end operational improvement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role sits within our EPM (Enterprise Performance Management) team in London, specifically within our reporting practice. We support our customers in producing complex reports more efficiently using technology, including things like Annual Reports, Statutory Reports, Fund Financial Statements, Sustainability Reporting, Fund Investor Reporting and more. Within our reporting practice, we primarily work with a tool called Workiva, of which we have a longstanding global partnership with. While Alpha Alternatives as a firm primarily supports alternative investment firms, our reporting practice supports customers across all industries that the wider Alpha group serve (Insurance, Asset Management, Banking and other Financial Services organisations).&lt;/p&gt;
