&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Azure Platform Engineer&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Role Summary&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an Azure Platform Engineer to lead the design and ongoing ownership of the Azure foundation supporting a multi-year municipal modernization program.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role helps to oversee Azure environment structure, CI/CD standards, and infrastructure-as-code strategy. All cloud resources must be provisioned and managed via IaC to ensure repeatability, auditability, and compliance across the program.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on engineering role with platform ownership responsibilities. Application engineers will rebuild business logic; this role ensures the cloud foundation they deploy into is secure, standardized, auditable, and production-ready.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Platform Architecture &amp;amp; Environment Ownership&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and manage dev, test, and production environments with strict separation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define secure networking, identity, and role-based access boundaries&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure VNETs, NSGs, private endpoints, and hybrid connectivity (VPN / ExpressRoute)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish standardized patterns for App Services, Azure SQL, storage, and shared services&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define platform standards to be used consistently across consolidated applications&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CI/CD &amp;amp; Deployment Standards&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and maintain standardized CI/CD pipelines in Azure DevOps&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop reusable pipeline templates and release patterns&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement approval gates, rollback strategies, and deployment controls aligned to audit requirements&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure consistent deployment practices across application teams&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all infrastructure deployments are executed through CI/CD pipelines using IaC templates (no manual provisioning)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Infrastructure as Code&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All infrastructure must be provisioned and maintained via Terraform or Bicep&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish IaC as the only approved deployment mechanism for cloud resources&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enforce code review, version control, and change traceability for all infrastructure changes&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prevent manual configuration drift across environments&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Security, Compliance &amp;amp; Observability&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embed FedRAMP Moderate–aligned controls into platform design&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement centralized logging, monitoring, and retention policies&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure Azure Policy and Defender for Cloud guardrails&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement secrets and certificate management using Azure Key Vault&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish audit traceability for infrastructure and deployment changes&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support disaster recovery and business continuity planning and testing&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Operational Excellence&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support production deployments and release windows&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot infrastructure and pipeline issues&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and maintain platform standards and operational runbooks&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement cost governance and resource optimization strategies&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Required Qualifications&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Bachelors’ deg

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercial Due Diligence Associate / Senior Associate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New York &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Alpha FMC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in London in 2003, Alpha FMC is a leading global consulting firm specializing in the financial services industry. Our 1,500+ consultants work across 19 offices worldwide, combining deep sector expertise with hands-on delivery to support more than 970 clients across asset management, wealth management, insurance, and broader financial services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are expanding our Commercial Due Diligence (CDD) offering within the Strategy &amp;amp; Deals team and are seeking experienced professionals to support high-profile buy-side and sell-side engagements for Private Equity investors and corporate clients. Our engagements deliver rigorous market, competitive, and commercial insight — enabling investors to make well-informed transaction decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Level Guidance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are open at both the Associate and Senior Associate level, depending on candidate experience:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Associate (A):1&lt;/strong&gt;+ years of relevant experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Associate (SA):&lt;/strong&gt; 3+ years of relevant experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The responsibilities below apply across both levels; Senior Associates are expected to take greater ownership of workstream and client delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engagements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead individual workstreams within CDD and growth-strategy projects, including market sizing, competitor benchmarking, and customer/expert research.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and analyze qualitative and quantitative data sets (market data, financials, interviews, surveys) to develop actionable, investor-grade insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support hypothesis development and contribute to client deliverables with clear, compelling storylines that stand up to IC scrutiny.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate data-driven and AI-supported analytics to enhance speed and depth of insight.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client &amp;amp; Stakeholder Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage directly with clients and expert networks to gather market intelligence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support client communications such as engagement updates and responding to requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Structure and present conclusions clearly to both technical and non-technical audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team &amp;amp; Practice&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise and coach junior team members, ensuring high-quality outputs and knowledge sharing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to internal knowledge development and business development efforts, including proposals and thought leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ to 3+ years of relevant experience in commercial due diligence (see Level Guidance above.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MBA preferred (or equivalent advanced degree/experience) for Senior Associates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills; comfort with both qualitative and quantitative analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills (written and verbal), with the ability to distill compl

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercial Due Diligence Engagement Lead / Engagement Director&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New York&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Alpha FMC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in London in 2003, Alpha FMC is a leading global consulting firm specializing in the financial services industry. Our 1,500+ consultants work across 19 offices worldwide, combining deep sector expertise with hands-on delivery to support more than 970 clients across asset management, wealth management, insurance, and broader financial services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are expanding our Commercial Due Diligence (CDD) practice within the Strategy &amp;amp; Deals team and are seeking a senior leader to drive high-profile buy-side and sell-side engagements in New York. This role focuses on market strategy, growth diagnostics, and commercial risk, providing investors and corporate clients with the insight needed to underwrite and defend transaction decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tenure Guidance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engagement Lead (EL):&lt;/strong&gt; 7–10 years of relevant experience, with exposure to M&amp;amp;A transactions and team leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engagement Director (ED):&lt;/strong&gt; 10+ years of relevant experience, with extensive subject-matter expertise, client ownership, and strategic advisory experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsibilities are structured to allow candidates to position themselves at the appropriate level based on experience, subject-matter depth, and deal ownership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The responsibilities below apply across both levels; Engagement Directors are expected to take greater ownership of client relationships and practice-level contribution, and will have a higher expectation for business development activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engagements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Commercial Due Diligence engagements end-to-end, covering market attractiveness, competitive positioning, customer economics, and growth strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Frame and test investor hypotheses on market growth, competitive dynamics, and commercial risk, identifying structural headwinds, customer concentration, and go-to-market constraints that could affect investment value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise clients on growth strategy, market positioning, and commercial risk mitigation, translating findings into actionable commercial and investment insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess target’s maturity relative to market best practice and peers within Financial Services, FinTech, and related B2B Services (commercial strategy, growth trajectory, customer economics, and competitive positioning).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Alpha&#39;s Technology DD, Operations DD, and Strategy teams to provide integrated perspectives on value creation and risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client &amp;amp; Stakeholder Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain senior client relationships, engaging with PE deal teams, portfolio company management teams, and bankers to inform transaction decisions and support value creation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take a lead role in shaping client communications, engagement direction, and IC-ready deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Structure and present conclusions clearly to both commercial and non-technical, IC-level audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team &amp;am

&lt;p&gt;Alpha Financial Markets Consulting (Alpha FMC) is the leading global consultancy to the asset and wealth management industry. We are a boutique management consulting firm that offers the world’s top asset and wealth managers a competitive edge through our expertise and industry insight. Our team is of a uniquely high calibre and by focusing on asset and wealth management alone we build deep knowledge and experience within our industry. We work with a blue-chip client base, including 95% of the top 20 global asset management firms, and work with over 660 clients across the globe. We have our headquarters located in the United Kingdom and operate out of 18 offices in the major financial centres to support our clients across the globe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our APAC team (Singapore, Malaysia, Sydney, Melbourne) is made up of consultants with deep expertise across the AWM industry. Our clients include Asset Owners, Managers and Servicers, Wealth Managers and Insurers. We provide our clients with a range of services covering Target Operating Models, Data Governance and Strategy, Implementations, Migrations, Benchmarking and Provider Selections. To clients, we are a trusted partner for creating programmes, however, we are so much more to our employees. At Alpha, we pride ourselves in being meritocratic environment perfect for building a career, meeting great people, as well as a rewarding place to work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In 2024, in recognition of our successful track record and strong growth prospects, Alpha was acquired by Bridgepoint, one of the world&#39;s leading quoted private asset growth investors. Our people are at the heart of everything we do. We are delighted that many of our team have built long and fulfilling careers with us, many staying over a decade. We believe this is because Alpha offers a genuinely rewarding place to work: a meritocratic environment where your career can flourish, and a welcoming culture where you can be yourself, connect with others and thrive. As we look to the future, we’re excited to be looking for new Alpha colleagues - individuals who are collaborative, innovative and ambitious. We hope you will join us and help shape the next chapter of our growth journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work, often with alongside a team, on client projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively participate in project and client meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce materials for business engagement meetings (e.g. PowerPoint decks)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support with creation of high-quality work products within expected timeframes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own key items for project delivery – including possible ownership of deliverables or work streams within a project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and monitor key project issues, risks, actions, and dependencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand Alpha FMC and its services and actively assess ways to serve clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay abreast of current business and industry trends relevant to the client&#39;s business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remain current on new developments in advisory services capabilities and industry knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support with the development of one or two internal business management areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Requirements (Skills, Experience and Qualifications):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 2-3 years of proven experience in the delivery of consulting or change projects gained within a leading financial institution or consulting firm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An understanding of market trends, drivers and outlook of the Asset and Wealth Management market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First-class communication, presentation and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stakeholder management and influencing skills – with both clients and colleagues&lt;/li&gt

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Alpha Group&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alpha Group is a leading global consultancy to the financial services industry. Founded in 2003, Alpha has spent over 20 years bringing together specialist, sector-focused strategy, management consulting, and technology expertise to support the entire client transformation lifecycle. Having partnered with more than 1,200 clients worldwide across the asset and wealth management, alternatives, and insurance industries, Alpha is a trusted advisor for complex change programs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We now have over 1,180 consultants working with clients across North America, the UK, Europe, the Middle East, and APAC. In 2024, in recognition of our successful track record and strong growth prospects, Alpha was acquired by Bridgepoint, one of the world&#39;s leading quoted private asset growth investors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our people are at the heart of everything we do. Many of our team have built long and fulfilling careers with us, often staying for over a decade. Alpha offers a genuinely rewarding place to work: a meritocratic environment where your career can flourish, and a welcoming culture where you can be yourself, connect with others, and thrive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we look to the future, we’re excited to be looking for new Alpha colleagues—individuals who are collaborative, innovative, and ambitious. We hope you will join us and help shape the next chapter of our growth journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why join Alpha?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexibility that supports real life&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;– We trust our team to manage their time and energy in the way that works best for them. Our hybrid and flexible working model allows you to balance client delivery with personal commitments — without sacrificing career progression.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inclusive parental leave &amp;amp; family support&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;– We offer generous parental leave for all parents alongside a truly supportive return-to-work culture. Many of our team members transition smoothly back through flexible scheduling, ramp-up periods, and ongoing mentorship.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Established yet entrepreneurial&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;– Alpha combines the stability of a global consultancy with the agility of a high-growth firm, giving you autonomy, visibility, and the ability to shape your career.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learning built in, not added on&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;– You’ll receive tailored training, structured mentorship, and up to 5 paid training days each year, plus on-the-job experience that accelerates your growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A diverse culture and leadership team&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;– We’re proud to have diversity within our senior leadership here at Alpha across North America and globally. We invest in developing all leaders through coaching, internal communities, and opportunities to work closely with partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A truly supportive environment&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;– We’re a meritocratic culture where your impact matters more than face time. We care about results, high standards, and collaboration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Consultant, you will be responsible for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engaging with stakeholders to drive and support execution against effective project plans, anticipate potential issues, and provide structured solutions to ensure a successful client engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading a workstream or component of a project, taking responsibility for the creation of client deliverables by facilitating client interviews and workshops, performing analysis in Excel, synthesizing clear insights from complex information, and developing content that clearly articulates recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helpin

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Location&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;New York, New Jersey, Connecticut&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MailCompose&quot;&gt;About Alpha FMC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alpha Financial Markets Consulting (Alpha) is a leading global consultancy to the financial services industry. Founded in 2003, we have worked for over 20 years to bring together specialist, sector-focused strategy, management consulting and technology expertise to support the entire client transformation lifecycle. Having partnered with more than 1,200 clients worldwide across the asset and wealth management, alternatives and insurance industries, Alpha is truly a trusted advisor for complex change programmes. We now have over 1,180 consultants working with clients across North America, the UK, Europe, Middle East and APAC. In 2024, in recognition of our successful track record and strong growth prospects, Alpha was acquired by Bridgepoint, one of the world&#39;s leading quoted private asset growth investors. Our people are at the heart of everything we do. We are delighted that many of our team have built long and fulfilling careers with us, many staying over a decade. We believe this is because Alpha offers a genuinely rewarding place to work: a meritocratic environment where your career can flourish, and a welcoming culture where you can be yourself, connect with others and thrive. As we look to the future, we’re excited to be looking for new Alpha colleagues - individuals who are collaborative, innovative and ambitious. We hope you will join us and help shape the next chapter of our growth journey.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Why join Alpha?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul data-border=&quot;0&quot; data-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-list-tree=&quot;true&quot; data-stringify-type=&quot;unordered-list&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Established yet entrepreneurial – &lt;/strong&gt;with over 20 years of success and a proven record on the London Stock Exchange, Alpha offers the stability of an established consultancy with the energy of a fast-growth business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Backed by Bridgepoint – &lt;/strong&gt;as part of one of the world’s leading growth investors, Alpha benefits from strategic investment that fuels innovation, expansion and new offerings – creating even more opportunity for our people.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exposure to senior leadership – &lt;/strong&gt;whether you are in an internal or a client facing role, you will have the opportunity to work with and learn from the best of the best – high performers at the top of their game.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learning and growth opportunities – &lt;/strong&gt;we run tailored training to help you be successful, provide you excellent mentorship, and offer up to 5 days paid training time per year. Perhaps the best training though is the experience on the job – as everyone at Alpha has high responsibility and autonomy, you can develop your skillsets quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance-driven culture with real impact – &lt;/strong&gt;advancement at Alpha is based on impact and capability, not tenure or quotas. You’ll have autonomy and see the tangible difference your ideas and decisions make.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a fast-growing team of dedicated consultants with deep experience from working both within the industry and consulting. Successful candidates should expect a diverse range of complex and strategic engagements across the Insurance market. As we continue to expand our client base and expertise, we are looking for individuals to join our team to support our growth journey. You will be

&lt;p&gt;Alpha Financial Markets Consulting (Alpha) is a leading global consultancy to the financial services industry. We are a boutique management consulting firm that offers the world’s top industry players a competitive edge through our expertise and industry insight. Our team is of a uniquely high calibre and by focusing across the General Insurance &amp;amp; Specialty value chain, we build deep knowledge and experience within our industry. We have our headquarters located the United Kingdom, as well as offices in major global financial centres across the United States, France, Netherlands, Luxembourg, Switzerland, and Asia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Insurance team works with industry leading carriers, brokers, market bodies, ancillary businesses, and technology providers to position our clients for future success. We have a fast growing team of dedicated consultants with deep experience from working both within the industry and consulting. Successful candidates should expect a diverse range of complex and strategic engagements across the market. As we continue to expand our client base and expertise, we are looking for individuals to join our team to support our growth journey. Please see below an outline of the responsibilities of the role as well as the requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working, both alongside a team and independently, on client projects, supporting project design through to delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting with the creation of high-quality work products within expected timeframes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Owning key items for project delivery – including possible ownership of deliverables or workstreams within a project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively participating in the preparation of materials for and delivery of project and client meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifying and internally discussing ideas for further business opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tracking and monitoring project plans and milestones, as well as key project issues, risks, actions,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;and dependencies, and escalating where appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing competing demands and priorities, from both internal and external stakeholders, to the satisfaction of all parties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding Alpha and its services and actively assessing ways to serve clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staying abreast of General Insurance &amp;amp; Specialty trends relevant to the client&#39;s business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Making a contribution to business development, supporting with the development of one or two internal business management areas (e.g. contributions to thought leadership, recruitment or Alpha proposition development)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Requirements (Skills, Experience and Qualifications):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successful candidates typically have around 3 years of proven experience in the delivery of consulting or change projects gained within a leading financial institution or consulting firm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant experience within ‘blue-chip’ Financial Services organisations, preferably within the General Insurance/ Specialty Insurance sectors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of projects engaged on Target Operating Model, business processes and/or IT solutions in some of the following areas: Broking, Underwriting &amp;amp; Distribution, Claims, Operations, IT, Data, Finance, Risk, Regulatory, outsourcing, cost optimisation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong stakeholder management and influencing skills – with both clients and colleagues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication, presentation, and problem-solving skills, confident at structuring and articulating messages and adapting communication style for different audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable proficiency in relationship development, preferable with business development/ account man

