&lt;h1&gt;Contract Manager&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Leeds&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team: &lt;/strong&gt;Legal, Compliance and Risk&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Division: &lt;/strong&gt;Business Services&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alpha FMC is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Contract Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to join our &lt;strong&gt;Legal, Compliance and Risk&lt;/strong&gt; team in Leeds.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alpha Financial Markets Consulting is a leading global consultancy to the financial services industry. Founded in 2003, we have worked for over 20 years to bring together specialist, sector-focused strategy, management consulting and technology expertise to support the entire client transformation lifecycle. Having partnered with more than 1,200 clients worldwide across the asset and wealth management, alternatives and insurance industries, Alpha is truly a trusted advisor for complex change programmes. We now have over 1,180 consultants working with clients across North America, the UK, Europe, Middle East and APAC. As we look to the future, we’re excited to be looking for new Alpha colleagues - individuals who are collaborative, innovative and ambitious. We hope you will join us and help shape the next chapter of our growth journey.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to become part of a trusted global function servicing our ever-evolving consultancy practice, that plays a key role in supporting Alpha’s growth, managing contractual relationships, and helping the business navigate legal, compliance and risk matters across its international operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Contract Manager, you will join a team that supports Alpha’s business activities globally, with Legal Services managing contractual engagement with clients, partners and vendors, alongside wider legal support to the business. &lt;br&gt;In this role, you will be responsible for supporting contract management across the business, including drafting and maintaining template documentation across Alpha’s business units, as well as providing support on a range of other legal matters on an ad hoc basis including, but not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing support to the business in respect of contractual relationships with new and existing clients, including reviewing, drafting and negotiating:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MSAs,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Terms and conditions of engagement,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SOWs,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NDAs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure contractual terms protect Alpha across key areas, such as liability, intellectual property, confidentiality, data protection, regulatory compliance, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support bid/proposal teams with contractual input during RFPs and pitch processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reviewing and negotiating supplier contracts, partnership arrangements, sub-contracts and other commercial contracts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring contracts comply with applicable law, industry regulations, and Alpha policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working closely with all Alpha’s business divisions, with primary focus on UK, MENA and APAC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What we’re looking for&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a candidate who brings strong legal and commercial judgement, excellent stakeholder management skills, and the ability to work effectively across multiple priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Essential requirements:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree-level qualification in law (English or other common law)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 3 years’ experience in a contract management role in a multi-national company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of contract law and contractual legal risk management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent negotiation and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and the ability to manage multiple priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&

